## 6. NanoPlot after filtering

After filtering with NanoFilt, NanoPlot should be run again to check how the length and quality distributions changed.

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

NanoPlot \
  --fastq NanoFilt_byBarcode/*.fastq.gz \
  -o NanoPlot_filtered_all \
  --threads 8 \
  --N50 \
  --plots kde hex dot \
  --title "NanoPlot - Filtered reads"

echo "✅ NanoPlot for filtered reads finished."
echo "📄 Report: NanoPlot_filtered_all/NanoPlot-report.html"

# Optional: open the report if working in a graphical Linux environment.
xdg-open NanoPlot_filtered_all/NanoPlot-report.html
```

### Expected result

```text
NanoPlot_filtered_all/
├── NanoPlot-report.html
├── *.png
└── *.txt
```

