## 7. Chimera removal with VSEARCH

Chimeras can be generated during PCR and may affect downstream taxonomic classification. They can be removed using `vsearch --uchime_denovo`.

### Recommendation

`vsearch --uchime_denovo` is typically run on FASTA files. Therefore, if the starting point is filtered FASTQ data, it is convenient to first convert the files to FASTA. One simple option is to use `seqkit`.

### Create a Conda environment with VSEARCH and SeqKit

```bash
conda create -n vsearch_env -c bioconda -c conda-forge vsearch seqkit
conda activate vsearch_env
```

### Script to remove chimeras from filtered FASTQ.gz files

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

INPUT_DIR="/home/mcharlo/Escritorio/Long_reads_Saliva_16S/First_run_lr_saliva/NanoFilt_byBarcode"
OUTPUT_DIR="/home/mcharlo/Escritorio/Long_reads_Saliva_16S/First_run_lr_saliva/NoChimera_NanoFilt"
TMP_DIR="$OUTPUT_DIR/tmp_fasta"

mkdir -p "$OUTPUT_DIR" "$TMP_DIR"

cd "$INPUT_DIR" || exit 1

echo "🔹 Chimera removal starting ..."

for fq in *.fastq.gz; do
  sample=$(basename "$fq" .fastq.gz)
  echo "🔄 Removing chimeras for $sample"

  fasta_tmp="$TMP_DIR/${sample}.fa"

  # Convert FASTQ.gz to FASTA.
  seqkit fq2fa "$fq" > "$fasta_tmp"

  # De novo chimera removal.
  vsearch --uchime_denovo "$fasta_tmp" \
    --nonchimeras "$OUTPUT_DIR/${sample}.nochim.fa" \
    --chimeras "$OUTPUT_DIR/${sample}.chimeras.fa" \
    --uchimeout "$OUTPUT_DIR/${sample}.uchime.txt"
done

echo "✅ Chimera removal complete."
echo "📁 Non-chimeric files saved in: $OUTPUT_DIR"
```

### Output files

For each sample/barcode, the script generates:

```text
sample.nochim.fa       # non-chimeric reads
sample.chimeras.fa     # reads identified as chimeric
sample.uchime.txt      # UCHIME result table/summary
```

